## 📊 SQL Queries

### 1. Inquiry to Sale Funnel
```sql
SELECT 
    stage,
    COUNT(*) AS total,
    ROUND(
        COUNT(*) * 100.0 / 
        FIRST_VALUE(COUNT(*)) OVER (ORDER BY stage_order), 1
    ) AS funnel_pct
FROM sales_pipeline
GROUP BY stage, stage_order
ORDER BY stage_order;
```
**Finding:** Identified exact drop-off point in inquiry-to-sale journey

---

### 2. Top Packages by Revenue
```sql
SELECT 
    package_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_sales,
    SUM(sale_value) AS total_revenue,
    ROUND(AVG(days_to_close), 1) AS avg_days_to_close
FROM sales
GROUP BY package_name
ORDER BY total_revenue DESC;
```
**Finding:** Top 3 packages drove majority of revenue

---

### 3. Peak Inquiry Period
```sql
SELECT 
    MONTHNAME(inquiry_date) AS month,
    product_type,
    COUNT(*) AS total_inquiries,
    SUM(CASE WHEN status = 'Converted' 
        THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS conversions,
    ROUND(
        SUM(CASE WHEN status = 'Converted' 
            THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(*), 1
    ) AS conversion_rate
FROM inquiries
GROUP BY MONTHNAME(inquiry_date), product_type
ORDER BY total_inquiries DESC;
```
**Finding:** Peak inquiry periods identified by product type and month

